      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand completely! Let's cut the goblin nonsense and get straight to the point. Here are the normal steps to fix your router:\n\n1.  **Check the cables:** Make sure the power cable is firmly plugged into the wall and the router. Also, verify that the Ethernet cable connecting your router to your modem (or the wall jack) is secure and not damaged.\n2.  **Power cycle:** Unplug the router from the wall outlet, wait about 30 seconds, and then plug it back in. Wait a minute or two for all the lights to stabilize.\n3.  **Check the modem:** If you have a separate modem, ensure it is also powered on and that its lights are normal (usually solid green or blue, not blinking red).\n4.  **Factory reset:** If nothing works, look for a small \"Reset\" hole on the back of the router. Use a paperclip to press it in for about 10 seconds. This will wipe settings and start fresh.\n5.  **Contact support:** If the lights still show red after these steps, there might be a line outage or a hardware failure, so you should call your Internet Service Provider (ISP) for",
